        • [ - ] DFox - member since 22-Mar-13

          As an Arsenal fan commenting, some interesting stats you can see in the chalkboard: * Only 3 efforts from open play to 8 Chelsea * 16 of 31 tackles attempted were successful. AMN with 6 out of 8. Torreira was 0 out of 4 (that was a surprise) * 12 interceptions but only 2 in Chelsea's half (Chelsea managed 8 in Arsenal's half) * 93 passes into Chelsea's final third compared to Chelsea making 175 into Arsenal's final third * Both teams attempted 21 dribbles. But Arsenal only successful with 10 compared to 15 for Chelsea. Nelson completed 1 of 6 attempts, often appearing to get caught down blind alleys. * Laca lost possession 6 times, the most of any player. He also failed to register a shot. Jorginho made a telling difference when coming on (aside from the issue of the 2nd yellow). He made 6 interceptions, the most of anyone in the match and provided the discipline and structure to change the game around. Credit to Lampard for making that change before half time.

        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          We were fantastic on the first half. Pressed intensely, found space, transitioned quickly and looked solid defensively despite holding a high defensive line. After Chelsea switched formation in the 2nd half, they were the better team. I'm not going to get on Leno's case when he has been our best player this season and spared our blushes on numerous occasions but I will get on Craig Pawson's. I'm not sure why he didn't give Jorginho a 2nd yellow when cynical fouls are a booking as standard. I don't expect referees to be perfect but this was an easy decision. A draw would have been the fair result but we defended like we have been all season to allow the winner. Hopefully Chambers' scan reveals his injury to not be as bad as I think it is.
